__NOTOC__ Year '191' ('[[Roman numerals|CXCI]]') was a common year starting on
Friday (link will display the full calendar) of the Julian calendar. At the
time, it was known as the 'Year of the Consulship of Apronianus and Bradua' (or,
less frequently, 'year 944Ab urbe condita'). The denomination 191 for this year
has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era
became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.
